Why do people use full tabs and put the braces at the indentation level of the opening statement?  I have discovered the one true coding style: 2 spaces indent, opening character immediately after opening statement, closing character on new line indented with preceding code block<p><pre><code>    how (
      is {
        this();
        }
      any();
      better(
        than[$parenthesis]
        );
      );</code></pre>
